# Training Dashboard

## Stack

- Next.js 15 App Router, React 19, TypeScript strict
- Tailwind CSS v4 + shadcn/ui (Base UI)
- Zustand (UI + filter state), Recharts (charts), PapaParse (CSV)

## Directory layout

- `src/app/` — routes only; keep route components thin
- `src/components/ui/` — shadcn primitives (do not business-logic here)
- `src/components/dashboard|import|layout/` — feature UI
- `src/lib/converters/` — one file per vendor format + `registry.ts`
- `src/lib/storage/` — `WorkoutRepository` implementations (`local-repository.ts` today)
- `src/types/` — domain types shared across UI and lib
- `src/hooks/` — client hooks and Zustand stores

## Domain model

Normalized type is `WorkoutSession` in `src/types/workout.ts`. All importers must output this shape. Session `id` is deterministic (see `src/lib/dedup.ts`).

## Adding a new import format

1. Add `src/lib/converters/my-app.ts` exporting a `WorkoutConverter` (`name`, `id`, `detect`, `convert`).
2. Register it in `src/lib/converters/registry.ts` (order: more specific detectors first).
3. If `detect` cannot be reliable without reading file bytes, prefer filename rules or document manual override in UI.

## Persistence

Use `getWorkoutRepository()` from `src/lib/storage/index.ts`. MVP uses `localStorage`. Future: add `SupabaseWorkoutRepository` implementing the same `WorkoutRepository` interface — do not query `localStorage` from components.

## Future integrations (stubs only until wired)

- **Supabase auth**: add a session provider in `AppProviders`; gate routes when needed.
- **RevenueCat**: gate premium widgets via a small `features` / `useSubscription` layer; keep free tier UI working without keys.

## AI / maintainability

- Prefer small files (<~200 lines); extract helpers over growing a single component.
- Use explicit types; avoid `any`.
- Add JSDoc on exported converter and repository public methods.
- Run `npm run lint` and `npm run build` after non-trivial changes.
